caption: b"Bath milk and freshly baked bread. Two things you never knew you needed, but Superhost Sonja has at the ready. In her mountain cabin just a short drive away from Jindabyne or Thredbo, there\xe2\x80\x99s open space, fresh air, and a fire to cozy up by. \xe2\x80\x9cYou will be cocooned in your hideaway from the crazy world,\xe2\x80\x9d Sonja says. In other words\xe2\x80\x94it's secluded, but still close enough for contactless food delivery (phew). \n\nDiscover new ways to holiday. Link in bio."

b'Winter wonderland might be closer than you think. Superhost Arthur\xe2\x80\x99s midcentury cabin is a cozily stylish place to flake out with loved ones over the holidays, whether you prefer board games by the fire or ice skating at nearby Santa\xe2\x80\x99s Village. Sleds included; not for rooftop use. \n\nPhoto: @palmstopeaks'

b'Fall gets all the glory, but there\xe2\x80\x99s no unspectacular time to visit Superhost Heather\xe2\x80\x99s cabin among the maples. Depending on when you get here, you can hike to Nichols Ledge for full-spectrum foliage, rent a fat-tired bike to ride through the snow, or lounge in the streamside hammock. It\xe2\x80\x99s all within a few hours of Boston, so maybe it\xe2\x80\x99s best to plan on one visit per season. 

Discover colorful places for the holidays near you. Link in bio. 

Photo: @stonecityvermont'

b'Give your favorite person a treehouse for the holidays. The views from Superhosts Rocky and Gianni\xe2\x80\x99s perch are breathtaking, and not just because you\xe2\x80\x99re at 8,000 feet. (The centuries-old fir it\xe2\x80\x99s built on is still alive, so who knows\xe2\x80\x94you might even be a hair higher by the time you leave.) World-class powder is a half-hour away, but be sure to stay home long enough to catch a glimpse of Marvin, the resident moose.\n\nPhoto: @thetreehouseutah'

b'Bright and full of life year-round, Superhost Ryan\xe2\x80\x99s rustic-chic chalet isn\xe2\x80\x99t your typical holiday cabin. But it\xe2\x80\x99s hardly been a typical year. Explore nearby Wiessner Woods or just hang out around the fire. If everyone heads for the door when you pick up the guitar, try not to be offended\xe2\x80\x94what better place to celebrate than a hot tub under the stars or snowflakes?\n\nPhoto: @om_home_residences'

b"Glow worms = nature's Christmas lights. These festive little friends will be some of your closest neighbors as you live your best off-the-grid life at this eco-escape. Be sure to end every night with soaks in the outdoor tub underneath the stars to feel complete illumination. \n\nDiscover ways to get together this holiday season. Link in bio."

b"It's a vibe: a cozy cabin, in the middle of nowhere, surrounded by beautiful nature. In Superhost's Kati's treehouse, you can spend the day making a holiday meal and then roast marshmallows over the outdoor fire pit before retreating onto the couch to binge-watch that show and scroll Instagram (are you doing that right now? Meta). \n\nDiscover new ways to holiday. Link in bio."

b'Feel like entering a different world for the holidays? You might not even have to leave town. A winding path through Japanese maples takes you to Superhost Danielle\xe2\x80\x99s handcrafted house near White Rock Lake. When it\xe2\x80\x99s time to gather around the table, you can put together an unconventional feast from a UN of nearby delivery options, from Tex-Mex to Lao. \n\nPhoto: @thedallastreehouse'

b"An hour outside of Bogot\xc3\xa1, there's a villa where you can make migas de arepa for your crew by morning (with fresh eggs from the chickens in the front yard) and chase waterfalls together along the Magdalena River in the afternoon. Be sure to stop by the local markets on your way in to stock up on roasted meats, fresh fruits for juices, and holiday street foods (bu\xc3\xb1uelos is a fave). \n\nDiscover new ways to get together this holiday season. Link in bio."

b'No one knows why, but conversations on porch swings count double. Superhost Galen\xe2\x80\x99s spacious cabin has lots of places to relax and reconnect over the holidays, including two fireplaces and a lakeside fire pit. Just as importantly, it also has a giant \xe2\x80\x9ccamp\xe2\x80\x9d room with bunk beds, games, and toys. Loving your family doesn\xe2\x80\x99t mean you won\xe2\x80\x99t crush them at air hockey.\n\nPhoto: @treetoplakehouse'

b'Cabin in the mountains, but make it tropical. This solar-powered, eco design cabin sits above the cloud-shrouded hills of the Brazilian countryside. By day, there\xe2\x80\x99s quiet mornings filled with birdsong and homegrown fresh fruit from Superhost Ken and Thierry. By night, there\xe2\x80\x99s the warmth of a crackling fire or good wine down at the fazenda. It\xe2\x80\x99s so remote, guests recommend an SUV to get up the hill (note, no one\xe2\x80\x99s concerned about how to get down). \n\nDiscover new ways to get together this holiday season. Link in bio.'

b'"You can\'t learn to roll dough by hand in school. Only from grandmas," says Online Experience host, Nonna Nerina. (That\xe2\x80\x99s grandma, in Italian). Join her and five of her friends as they share their lifelong recipes from their virtual kitchens and learn how to make handmade gnocchi, lasagne, or fettuccine from scratch. It\xe2\x80\x99s like snapping your fingers and being transported to a remote Roman village with your adopted Italian grandma. Link in bio.'

b'This beachfront A-frame isn\xe2\x80\x99t short on spaces to reflect together: in the soaking tub, the hot sauna, or face-to-face with a glacier at Kenai Fjords National Park nearby. If you need help staying rooted through the holidays, the local spruce trees can offer some advice\xe2\x80\x94or you can book a private (socially-distanced) group yoga class with Superhost KellyAnn. \n\nDiscover new ways to get together this holiday season. Link in bio.'

b'Grab a blanket, bring someone close to you a little closer, and watch the moon rise over the Mission Mountains. This cozy cabin is perfect for a back-to-basics holiday getaway. When you feel like exploring, Stephanie, your Superhost, will point you toward her favorite scenic drives (not that there are many unscenic ones around here).\n\nPhoto: @cmpereira87'

b'Superhost Jake designed his holiday-ready cabin for conversation and togetherness, so there\xe2\x80\x99s no TV. But it does have a highly bingeable fireplace, easy access to ski slopes, and a national forest in the backyard. Last-minute gift idea: a box of cinnamon bear claws from Dank Donuts, a short walk away. \n\nPhoto: @bigbeartreehouse'

b'These homes aren\xe2\x80\x99t just beautiful. They\xe2\x80\x99re realizations of ideas, of imagined outcomes, years of hard work, of obstacles overcome. When you want to do something big, bring yourself to a place that reminds you what can happen when someone who has a vision finally takes pen to paper, hammer to nail. Somewhere you can sit quietly and coax out your courage to start, and then to continue.

b'Where better to reach for the stars than high up on jungle-covered mountains, smack-dab in the center of San Crist\xc3\xb3bal?  Sit down in Superhost Diego\xe2\x80\x99s colorful, colonial-style home at its laptop-friendly workstations or in its peaceful courtyard and start that project that your heart wants but your brain thinks is impossible. \xc2\xa1Si se puede!'

caption: b'Though inspired by a certain author of children\xe2\x80\x99s books, Superhosts Jordan and Dan\xe2\x80\x99s treehouse isn\xe2\x80\x99t just for kids. b'When your person takes you here, the least you can do is wait patiently for your walk to the lake. Less than two hours from L.A., Superhost Giulia\xe2\x80\x99s elegant A-frame also has plenty of space for the family to get together for the holidays, whether that means board games, patrolling for squirrels, or staking out the warmest patch of sun on the floor.

b'Golden opportunities are rarely this obvious about it. Framed by fall foliage or covered in snow, David\xe2\x80\x99s cabin in the Poconos might be your family\xe2\x80\x99s next holiday tradition. b'At Superhost Elijah\xe2\x80\x99s boulder-top cabin, the only screens to watch are the big windows on every side. b'Want to hang on a South African beach with endangered penguins? Starting today, (virtually) travel the world and try @AirbnbExperiences from home \xe2\x80\x94like "the Art of Penguin Conservation" with Online Experience host, Jon.

b'The hike up nearby Mt. Monadnock leads to some unforgettable views, but the true peak of your holidays might be coming home afterward to Superhost John\xe2\x80\x99s cozy cottage. b'An hour or so from Nashville, Superhost Anna\xe2\x80\x99s cabin is a cozy home base for exploring some great state parks\xe2\x80\x94Cummins Falls, Burgess Falls, and Standing Stone, to name a few. b'Inspired design inspires. If you\xe2\x80\x99re looking to spark your creative fire, you can surround yourself with both natural and man-made beauty at Superhost Eric\xe2\x80\x99s Alianz Loft. What better to propel you into your own future than an (almost) literal spaceship? And bunnies?'

b'Looking for a creative spark, and the space to let it ignite? Superhosts Stephanie and Nathan packed a few tons of inspiration into this loft in the Dutra, their eclectic downtown mini-inn. When you\xe2\x80\x99re hungry, al fresco options abound in Little Italy, a few blocks away. #GoNear

b'A cowboy tub big enough for your whole posse is just one of the special touches at this high-desert hideaway two hours from Los Angeles. b'An afternoon\xe2\x80\x99s drive from Boston, Superhost Stephanie\xe2\x80\x99s airy loft invites you to slow down and change your perspective above a glacial lake. b"Vibrant color and celebration isn\xe2\x80\x99t the vibe you\xe2\x80\x99d expect from a holiday called Dia de los Muertos (the Day of the Dead). Online Experience host Marisol from Mexico City explains, \xe2\x80\x9cthe Aztecs believed we should celebrate, not grieve, the lives of our loved ones.\xe2\x80\x9d 

In Marisol's experience, \xe2\x80\x9cTraditions of Mexico\xe2\x80\x99s Day of the Dead,\xe2\x80\x9d you\xe2\x80\x99ll learn how to build an ofrenda (altar) that includes all the four earth elements. Papel picado (pictured) represents air and the fragility of life. Spend an hour and a half in Mexico (virtually) and make a sugar skull dedicated to someone who has passed (yes, historically they were made of real sugar and you can eat the version Marisol teaches you to make). Life, after all, is sweet. 

:camera::: @octaviocortesfotografia"

b'What if you could put a love spell\xe2\x80\xa6on yourself? \xe2\x80\x9cYou speak things into existence,\xe2\x80\x9d says host Jasmine in Los Angeles. \xe2\x80\x9cA spell is basically a ritual. A self-love spell is when you use the power of intention to manifest the things you desire, like having more confidence and loving yourself.\xe2\x80\x9d

In her Online Experience, \xe2\x80\x9cSelf-Love Spell Creation Course,\xe2\x80\x9d Jasmine (@dreamgirlspirituality) culls from over 20 years of tarot card and spell-making experience to help people bring rituals into their every day life. \xe2\x80\x9cTimes are rough, especially now,\xe2\x80\x9d she says, thumbing through one of her many tiny journals filled with hand-written spells. \xe2\x80\x9cI just want to help people find hope. Find a little bit of magic every day.\xe2\x80\x9d 

Tap into your magical abilities this Halloween. Link in bio + see more in our stories

Carnival takes many forms, but it\xe2\x80\x99s always an experience to remember\xe2\x80\x94especially when you have a special place where you can catch your breath between the festivities, like Cannelle\xe2\x80\x99s cliffside villa in Guadeloupe or Udo\xe2\x80\x99s Moorish-style castle on Tenerife. With equally special spots in Rio de Janeiro, Venice, and New Orleans, just to name a few, the possibilities are endless.'

b'Contemplating the F\xc3\xb8rde Fjord from Superhost Torstein\xe2\x80\x99s cubic cabin might be the world\xe2\x80\x99s best way to think inside the box. Hike the surrounding mountains or just follow the cows and sheep as they wander the wild landscape. In summer, wait until about midnight before heading down to the water for a sunset swim.\n\nPhoto: @cheyennedekeyser'

b'Superhost Jay\xe2\x80\x99s elegant apartment is perched on the coast of Yeong-do, the island that forms one corner of the city. If it\xe2\x80\x99s your first time here, get your bearings by climbing Jangsan, a mountain just outside of town with views of the whole area. Once you come down, it\xe2\x80\x99s up to you whether to spend your time deep inside this tub or deep inside a bowl of bibim milmyeon, the spicy local noodle specialty.\n\nPhoto: @so__nni_'

b'The Bahamas\xe2\x80\x99 natural gifts go far beyond sun, sea, and sand. As part of The Bahamas Sabbatical, you\xe2\x80\x99ll explore local botanical traditions with farmers and gardeners on the island of Eleuthera. You\xe2\x80\x99ll discover the healing properties of native plants, learn to make bush tea and other remedies, and even help conduct workshops to promote these deep-rooted traditions.\n\nApply by 11:59pm EST on February 18, 2020. Terms and conditions apply.'

b'This studio in a 17th-century building across from the Duomo is for solo travelers only, but please don\xe2\x80\x99t do anything rash. Instead of breaking up with your partner to come here, consider booking it for them after you\xe2\x80\x99ve had your turn. Dani, your Superhost, designed the place for creative solitude, but you\xe2\x80\x99ll hardly feel alone. Just ask and she\xe2\x80\x99ll point you to her favorite walks and restaurants away from the crowds.\n\nPhoto: @girlgoneabroad'

b'Wake up with the roosters and you can be on Corong Corong Beach by sunrise. Judex, your host, is happy to help you plan adventures all around the Bacuit Archipelago. One idea: kayak across the bay to Cadlao Island for a day of snorkeling and exploring.\n\nPhoto: @travelisforlovers_'

b'There\xe2\x80\x99s no such thing as a bad view of Lake Como, but Cristina\xe2\x80\x99s bright apartment has one of the best. Midway between Como and Bellagio, the place is far enough from the crowds to let you soak up the beauty in peace. But it\xe2\x80\x99s also centrally located\xe2\x80\x94a short walk takes you to a pier where you can catch ferries that\xe2\x80\x99ll take you all around the lake.\n\nPhoto: @a_choe13'
b'Be one of 5 volunteers to join Airbnb for a once in a lifetime opportunity to help preserve the traditions and become part of the Bahamian community.'

b'The Bahamas\xe2\x80\x99 marine ecosystem is one of the most diverse in the world. Keeping it that way takes a lot of work. As a member of The Bahamas Sabbatical, you\xe2\x80\x99ll team up with lifelong local divers and fishermen in Exuma to learn ethical fishing practices that protect both the ecosystem and the local fishing industry.\n\nApply by 11:59pm EST on February 18, 2020. Terms and conditions apply.'

b'Superhost Gonzalo put his own slant on the tiny home by building this unique little refuge. Just off the Carretera Austral\xe2\x80\x94the road that snakes through some of northern Patagonia\xe2\x80\x99s most spectacular places\xe2\x80\x94it\xe2\x80\x99s an ideal spot to catch your breath. Gonzalo can also help you decide where to eat in town (20 minutes away) and where to go next.\n\nPhoto: @insidemyday'

b'Hand-built of wood cut right on the property, this tiny solar-powered retreat lets you disconnect from the grid and recharge your own internal batteries. The surrounding 170 acres are home to a wide range of wildlife, from blue herons to white-tailed deer. But the real star is Buffalo Creek, where you can swim, fish, canoe, or just watch as it flows by.\n\nPhoto: @yuliyablain'

b'The only downside of Superhost Magnus\xe2\x80\x99s house is the high risk of HTRF (hot tub raisin fingers) caused by its mesmerizing archipelago view. The place is perfectly situated for guests who want to relax into nature\xe2\x80\x94at home or in nearby Tyresta National Park\xe2\x80\x94while staying within easy reach of the city.\n\nPhoto: @daisylovesplaces'

b'Superhost Nin\xe2\x80\x99s airy home on an artist\xe2\x80\x99s estate is ideal for unwinding and reconnecting with a loved one. If you forget to bring your own, seek out Oscar, the reportedly cuddly rabbit who lives on the property. When you feel like venturing out, stroll into town for a farm-fresh brunch at Shindig\xe2\x80\x94maybe grab a carrot to bring home\xe2\x80\x94or serious artisanal ice cream at Nancy\xe2\x80\x99s.\n\nPhoto: @raexraes'

b"Remember planking? Um, neither do we. A lot has changed since 2010, but here's one thing that hasn\xe2\x80\x99t: the desire to experience unforgettable homes and places around the world. From a palatial Tuscan villa to a remote Brazilian beach house, here are some of the most wish-listed homes of the past decade. Click the link in bio to explore the whole list."

b'With all due respect to standard, single A-frames, once you\xe2\x80\x99ve gone double, it\xe2\x80\x99s tough to go back. Superhost Laura\xe2\x80\x99s tiny cabin is just part of a compound of equally creative little homes. Team up with friends to take over the whole spread, or start here and make new friends by the fire pit. When you\xe2\x80\x99re hungry, grab a cruiser bike and head to Gaskins in town for a meal straight from nearby farms.\n\nPhoto: @gatherwildranch'

b'The view from this modern apartment on the Sarnersee is undeniable, but by the end of your stay, it might not be what you appreciate most. Roland, your Superhost, grew up here and will happily point you to his favorite hikes, restaurants, and day trips, both on and well off the beaten track.\n\nPhoto: @villa_wilen'

b"Superhost Michael\xe2\x80\x99s tiny cabin packs everything you need into one bright little package. Nearby outdoor options abound. If you make it here before the snow melts, hit the slopes of Stowe Mountain Resort. If you don't, hop in a canoe at Green River Reservoir State Park.\n\nPhoto: @sunrise_sunset_tiny_house"

b'Tiny cabin on the outside, luxury condo on the inside. Superhosts Micah and Jules have created an ideal base for adventures in Zion National Park (a spectacular half-hour drive away), Bryce Canyon, and the Grand Staircase. But there\xe2\x80\x99s also plenty of beauty closer to home, under the white cliffs of East Zion. Recent guests recommend hiking in nearby Kanab, as well as the Superhosts\xe2\x80\x99 guided slot canyon experiences.\n\nPhoto: @mod3design'

b'Superhost Katy\xe2\x80\x99s bright apartment is the perfect place to recharge between explorations. Climb nearby Calton Hill to get your bearings, and then dive in\xe2\x80\x94the whole city center is within walking distance. At night, check out Bedlam Theatre, a student-run playhouse inside an appropriately dramatic neo-Gothic church.\n\nPhoto: @melchiorskingdom'

b'Even giants need a helping hand sometimes. As part of The Bahamas Sabbatical, you\xe2\x80\x99ll join a local conservationist to help restore the Andros Barrier Reef\xe2\x80\x94the third-largest living organism on the planet. After learning proper techniques, you\xe2\x80\x99ll dive in and collect, nurture, and transplant coral, helping to sustain the reef that sustains so much other life in The Bahamas. \nApply by 11:59pm EST on February 18, 2020. Terms and conditions apply.'

b'Superhost Rebecca\xe2\x80\x99s big house above the ocean has so many cozy corners that it can be tough to get out. But the beach is only a short walk away. After a day of hiking or whale-watching, head to Spud Point Crab Company for the catch of the day, straight off the owner\xe2\x80\x99s boat.\n\nPhoto: @earthtoandrea'

b'Now that you know floor hammocks are a thing, you owe it to yourself to try one. Make sure your first time is special by preparing as follows: 1. Book David\xe2\x80\x99s A-frame in the Poconos; 2. Spend the day on the slopes of nearby Camelback Mountain Resort; 3. Have a soak in the hot tub. Now you\xe2\x80\x99re ready. Just be prepared to wake up checkered and happy the next day.\n\nPhoto: @alpine_a_frame'

b'The Bahamas Sabbatical is a once-in-a-lifetime chance to experience\xe2\x80\x94and help restore\xe2\x80\x94the islands\xe2\x80\x99 natural and cultural beauty. Five volunteers will spend April and May working alongside passionate local hosts restoring the Andros Barrier Reef, practicing ethical fishing in The Exumas, and helping preserve native bush tea in Eleuthera. \nApply by 11:59pm EST on February 18, 2020. Terms and conditions apply. Link in bio.'

b'Tucked between the jungle and the beach, Superhost Luciana\xe2\x80\x99s spacious villa is a minute\xe2\x80\x99s walk from the waves. If you feel like venturing inland, check out the mangrove forests of Laguna de Manialtepec. Just be sure to be home for dinner\xe2\x80\x94the included chef service is a nightly showcase for treasures like pescado zarandeado (traditional wood-fired fish). Photo: @casa_cal'

b'Superhost Michelle\xe2\x80\x99s high-desert retreat offers an unbeatable sunrise/sunset double feature with an occasional guest appearance by a blanket of snow. In between showtimes, head to nearby Joshua Tree National Park and hike among the massive boulders of the Hidden Valley Nature Trail.\n\nPhoto: @bighorn_homestead'

b'Superhost Michelle\xe2\x80\x99s high-desert retreat offers an unbeatable sunrise/sunset double feature with an occasional guest appearance by a blanket of snow. In between showtimes, head to nearby Joshua Tree National Park and hike among the massive boulders of the Hidden Valley Nature Trail.\n\nPhoto: @bighorn_homestead'

b'Superhost Jean-Maxime wants to make your stay at her unique cabin as special as the design. That\xe2\x80\x99s why she bundles each day\xe2\x80\x99s breakfast in a basket you lift to the terrace with a pulley. Breakfast might not be your most memorable meal here, though\xe2\x80\x94Restaurant Paul Bocuse is right across the Sa\xc3\xb4ne River. Despite a lack of pulleys, the food is reportedly pretty decent.\n\nPhoto: @labengale'

b'Superhost Mafe\xe2\x80\x99s cabin sits above the spectacular Embalse del Pe\xc3\xb1ol, the sprawling reservoir that helps set Antioquia apart from just about everywhere else. The cabin is equally well suited for those who want to bask in the view (with a birdsong soundtrack) and those who\xe2\x80\x99d rather grab the included kayak and explore the reservoir\xe2\x80\x99s countless inlets.\n\nPhoto: @momotcabin'

b'This treehouse is only a ferry ride and short drive from Auckland but feels like a true escape. Maybe it\xe2\x80\x99s the native birdsong, an enchanting soundtrack even if you wouldn\xe2\x80\x99t know a morepork from a kerer\xc5\xab. Catch up on your reading, soak in the spring water hot tub, or have lunch at nearby Man O\xe2\x80\x99 War Vineyards\xe2\x80\x94just your everyday winery on the beach.\n\nPhoto: @sapanatravels'

b'You know you\xe2\x80\x99re in Oaxaca when your front yard is a mezcal museum. Speaking of local specialties, Superhost Carlos says there\xe2\x80\x99s no better place for tlayudas\xe2\x80\x94the classic flatbread street snack\xe2\x80\x94than right in the neighborhood at Tlayudas Do\xc3\xb1a Flavia. When you\xe2\x80\x99re ready to venture out, both the state capital and Mitla, the ancient Zapotec site, are a short drive away.\n\nPhoto: @myhaus'

b"This Valentine's Day, the home of Shakespeare's Juliet is available for one night only on Airbnb. Follow in the footsteps of the star-crossed lovers as you explore one of the world's most romantic cities. 
Enter to win by 11:59pm EST Feb 2, '20. Rules apply.

Tap the link in our bio for details."

b'Not that you need to justify spending half of your stay in this tub, but if it makes you feel better, you can wear yourself out first with a vigorous hike from the nearby Idyllwild Nature Center. Just be sure to beat your friends back to Superhost Anthony\xe2\x80\x99s lovingly restored 1962 chalet.\n\nPhoto: @idyllhaus'

b'Superhost Quinn\xe2\x80\x99s Catskills cottage sits on 12 serene acres lined by old stone walls. After a day of wandering local trails or skiing Plattekill Mountain, head to Peekamoose, a cozy spot featuring ingredients from nearby farms and\xe2\x80\x94if you\xe2\x80\x99re there on the right night\xe2\x80\x94warm brioche doughnuts for dessert.\n\nPhoto: @mountainthymecottage'

b'Eiwa\xe2\x80\x99s dome cabin on the edge of town makes it easy to explore the region\xe2\x80\x99s beauty, both natural and human-made. Hike among the sculptures of El Bosque Tallado (the Carved Forest) or cool off in the turquoise waters of R\xc3\xado Azul. On your way home, stop for dessert in the lush garden of Caf\xc3\xa9 Paseo de las Flores.\n\nPhoto: @eiwadomos'

b'Stay inside a replica Conestoga settler\xe2\x80\x99s wagon within easy reach of Hill Country vineyards and state parks. You can\xe2\x80\x99t drive it, even if you bring your own horses, but you can walk to The Club, right on the property, for an eclectic meal and live local music.\n\nPhoto: @kristen_cook'

b'At Eduardo\xe2\x80\x99s loft overlooking Playa de Quintay, the toughest decision you\xe2\x80\x99ll face is whether to spend the day above the waves or far beneath them, scuba diving among wrecked whaling ships. Either way, be sure to head to the pier afterward for fresh fish to grill on your deck while the whole coast turns pink.\n\n@rafael_medeiros'

b'The A in this A-frame is for Anabela, a Superhost who loves giving guests a taste of country living only 12 miles from Durham. Wander the woods on the property or head into town for a farm-to-table meal at Piedmont and an equally fresh concert at the Carolina Theatre.\n\nPhoto: @leeannchisolmmorrissette'

b'Superhost Olivia\xe2\x80\x99s cozy house on a windswept field is perfect for quiet reflection. But it\xe2\x80\x99s also a great home base for exploring the lochs, canals, and ancient forests of the Highlands along the Great Glen Way. On your way out, fuel up in town with Scotch pie at the Redburn Cafe.\n\nPhoto: @elle.ho'

b'If you think these plants look happy in this light, wait until you see what it does for humans. Superhosts Matt and Ron turned their penthouse loft into a re-energizing urban oasis. Not that the surrounding area is a desert\xe2\x80\x94sprawling Victoria Park is a block away. When you\xe2\x80\x99re hungry, keep the blooming theme going at Scarecrow, a unique combination florist-caf\xc3\xa9.\n\nPhoto: @mrcigar'

b'Superhosts Ulrich and Elisabeth\xe2\x80\x99s eco-retreat on a roadless island has a coral reef for a front yard and a mangrove forest out back. Explore the lagoon by snorkel or kayak or take a cue from the tree sloths who\xe2\x80\x99ll (eventually) visit and just slow down.\n\nPhoto: @soyyiana'

b'Don\xe2\x80\x99t bring a good book into this bed or you might never make it out. That\xe2\x80\x99d be a shame, since this midcentury A-frame puts you so close to so many classic Oregon Coast pleasures. Dig for clams at Netarts or Tillamook Bay, follow endless hiking trails through coastal rainforest, or ask your Superhost, Emily, about her favorite local spots.\n\nPhoto: @gisellewaters'

b'Elizabeth\xe2\x80\x99s handbuilt 1957 mountain home is only 10 minutes from the shops and street performers of Pearl Street, but you\xe2\x80\x99d never know it. Kick back and soak up the winter sun\xe2\x80\x94and a panoramic view of the Rockies\xe2\x80\x99 Front Range\xe2\x80\x94or grab your snowboard and head out to Eldora Mountain.\n\nPhoto: @sunshinelodgeco'

b'The narrow 14th-century streets of Bukchon Hanok Village can make you lose track of where\xe2\x80\x94or when\xe2\x80\x94you are. This renovated hanok in the heart of the neighborhood can have the same effect (at least until you use the distinctly 21st-century toiletries). Check out the two palaces that flank the neighborhood or ask your Superhost, Han, for local tips while savoring the traditional breakfast he provides each day.\n\nPhoto: @analog_hanok_in_bukchon'

b'The downside of a place as cozy as Superhost Elsa\xe2\x80\x99s tiny home is that it tends to make you rip through your reading material. Head to Malaprop\xe2\x80\x99s Bookstore/Cafe to replenish your supply. When you\xe2\x80\x99re ready for some real-life adventure, the trails of Mt. Mitchell are within a short drive along the spectacular Blue Ridge Parkway.\n\nPhoto: @_jonathanaguirre'

b'Superhost Kay\xe2\x80\x99s apartment puts you in the heart of the lovely old Bergmannkiez neighborhood. To get your bearings, climb the hill in Viktoriapark for a view of the city. (If it\xe2\x80\x99s snowy, you can sled back down.) For lunch, walk to the 19th-century Marheineke Markthalle and prepare to be overwhelmed with options.\n\nPhoto: @spardhamalik'

b'Superhosts Sara and Eric\xe2\x80\x99s midcentury chalet is equally well suited for hitting the slopes or hanging out by the fire (or in a sunny spot on the floor). A shuttle to Big Bear Mountain Resort is a short walk away. If you ever want a break from the ski/apr\xc3\xa8s-ski cycle, check out Big Bear Alpine Zoo, which rehabilitates and releases injured native wildlife.\n\nPhoto: @treehauschalet'

b"Surrounded by 17,000 foot peaks, Superhost Ashima's Manali home offers an escape from the hustle and bustle of city life. Spend your day admiring the landscape, which changes depending on the way the sun hits or when a cloud goes by. If you're looking to meet the locals, the village is only a 20 minute walk downhill, with communal hot springs and temples dating back thousands of years.\n\nExplore remote homes around the world in Airbnb Magazine through the link in our bio. :camera:: @markhartman"

b'In the corner of Vermont known as the Northeast Kingdom, this treehouse above Walker Pond is one of the most regal castles. After a day on the slopes of Jay Peak Resort, have a soak in the handmade cedar tub. When you get hungry, nearby Newport has some great new places to try, though you might have a hard time outdoing the waffles and local syrup provided by your Superhosts, Andrew and Marilou.\n\nPhoto: @ashleysantos4619'
